annotationA: Pms2; Mismatched DNA binding; ATP binding; MutSalpha complex binding; single-stranded DNA binding; ATPase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: reciprocal meiotic recombination; mismatch repair
annotationB: Nucleotide excision repair protein ERCC1; Ercc1 is the non-catalytic partner of the mei-9 nuclease that cuts structures formed during DNA repair. The mei-9-Ercc1 heterodimer interacts with mus312 to make meiotic crossovers. Ercc1 functions include repair of UV-induced DNA damage, repair of base adducts, a backup pathway for mismatch repair and meiotic recombination
